WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.780
Hello and welcome back. In this lesson, I will show you an easy way to fix all your open claw

00:00:05.780 --> 00:00:12.860
problems using AI using the Codex app. The Codex app is included with your ChatGPT subscription.

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:20.120
All you have to do is to download and use it. With a normal ChatGPT chat, you typically need

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:26.200
to copy error messages and code into the chat window and let it output the solution. Then you

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:31.640
would copy the solution out and paste it into your machine or manually edit your

00:00:31.640 --> 00:00:36.760
local files based on the suggested solution. However, if you have the Codex

00:00:36.760 --> 00:00:42.760
app installed, you tell it your problem and ask it to fix it directly. You then

00:00:42.760 --> 00:00:48.640
give full access to your PC and it will directly access the files and do the fix.

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:54.340
Don't worry, it is quite safe. You can set the level of access and permission. It

00:00:54.340 --> 00:00:58.840
It could ask you to approve certain actions before it proceeds.

00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:02.900
Head over to its official website to read all about it.

00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:09.640
Codex is OpenAI's coding agent and is included with ChatGPT Plus subscription.

00:01:09.640 --> 00:01:15.680
It can write code, understand and explain complex code and explain it to you.

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.860
Check your code to identify problems and fix them.

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:21.860
And much more.

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:28.420
you can give it access to your PC, it can perform all those tasks effectively and efficiently,

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:35.940
saving you a lot of headache. Let's download it now. There is also a CLI command line interface

00:01:35.940 --> 00:01:42.820
version, but the app version is easier to use as it has a graphical user interface like ChatGPT.

00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:50.180
But before we install it, let us take a snapshot of our virtual machine where we had already

00:01:50.180 --> 00:02:05.490
installed deep seek version 4 pro. Give it a suitable name. You could also take snapshots

00:02:05.490 --> 00:02:10.370
from the oracle virtual box manager but the virtual machine needs to be shut down first.

00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:24.630
Now we download the installer for the codex app. Go to the downloads folder and double click to begin

00:02:24.630 --> 00:02:38.600
the installation. There is a notice saying: "Included with all chat gpt plans". Click continue with chat

00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:44.840
GPT. I normally use my Google account to authenticate. Just login with the method

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:54.440
you normally use to login to chat GPT. Click on continue. This is optional. Just select the type

00:02:54.440 --> 00:03:00.680
of work you do so that it will customize codex for you. You can skip this step if you like.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:07.960
You could try GPT 5.5 but I find that you might hit the rate limit faster.

00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:14.920
I prefer GPT 5.4 which might have higher quotas allowing you to go longer before hitting the rate

00:03:14.920 --> 00:03:22.600
limits. Just click try button or close this dialog. You can change model later. Here is where you set

00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:31.880
the model you want. Select GPT 5.4 with medium setting. Now I give it full access to my machine.

00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:46.790
Next step is to pin it to the taskbar so that we can launch it easily again in future.

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:51.830
This is needed because it does not have a desktop shortcut.

00:03:53.190 --> 00:04:09.880
Let's test the new taskbar icon. And it works. You can access the documentation and help here.

00:04:15.650 --> 00:04:19.570
You can tile the windows by hovering your mouse over the maximize icon.

00:04:20.210 --> 00:04:26.210
Then select the tile pattern you want. You can also collapse the sidebar menus.

00:04:26.210 --> 00:04:41.060
Let's type in hello.

00:04:41.060 --> 00:04:45.080
It wants us to set up the agent sandbox first.

00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:54.000
So we click on the setup button. Confirm it.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:05:03.640
Now send the hello message. And it replies.

00:05:03.640 --> 00:05:06.840
So it is just like chat GPT.

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:15.010
Now we are going to ask it to create a folder on the desktop.

00:05:15.010 --> 00:05:20.870
Then ask it to write a simple hello program in python and put it in that folder.

00:05:20.870 --> 00:05:33.050
The program will ask for our name and then print a hello message with our name.

00:05:33.050 --> 00:05:37.290
It asks for confirmation and I confirm it.

00:05:37.290 --> 00:05:41.150
It completes the task and tells us how to run the program.

00:05:41.150 --> 00:05:44.750
On the desktop, I notice the new folder called greeting app.

00:05:44.750 --> 00:05:46.110
Let's enter the folder.

00:05:46.110 --> 00:05:50.170
To run it, I right click and select open in terminal.

00:05:50.170 --> 00:05:52.790
A PowerShell window opens.

00:05:52.790 --> 00:05:59.580
I then type Python followed by the name of the program.

00:05:59.580 --> 00:06:03.500
I enter my name and it prints, Hello Paul.

00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:07.800
It works.

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:11.160
On the left sidebar menu, we can open new chats.

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:15.000
And there is also a list of previous chats.

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:17.660
There is so much more Codex can do.

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:20.340
This is only a quick taste of its power.

00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:26.160
You can tell it where you install OpenClaw and ask it to configure new models for you.

00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:31.600
If open claw is not working as expected, just describe your problem and ask it to fix it

00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:32.600
for you.

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:34.280
That's all for this video.

00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:35.260
Thanks for watching.

